This seems to be a bug in our website. The whl files are there but we just dont have the links there.
@wollf can we route this appropriately to update the link and the website?

In the meantime, you can replace all 35 in the python 3.5 links with 36 to download the pip package for python 3.6
Or you can simply use pip install tensorflow to get the appropriate pip package from pypi.

body:
This seems to be a bug in our website. The whl files are there but we just dont have the links there.
@wollf can we route this appropriately to update the link and the website?

In the meantime, you can replace all `35` in the python 3.5 links with `36` to download the pip package for python 3.6
Or you can simply use `pip install tensorflow` to get the appropriate pip package from pypi.
